# Awesome Subagents Catalog

- Source: `.codex/agents/*.toml`
- Installed location: `Developer/agent_room/*.toml`
- Installed count: 138
- Note: existing project-custom TOML files in `Developer/agent_room` were preserved instead of overwritten.

## Installed Agents

- `accessibility-tester` - Use when a task needs an accessibility audit of UI changes, interaction flows, or component behavior.
- `ad-security-reviewer` - Use when a task needs Active Directory security review across identity boundaries, delegation, GPO exposure, or directory hardening.
- `agent-installer` - Use when a task needs help selecting, copying, or organizing custom agent files from this repository into Codex agent directories.
- `agent-organizer` - Use when the parent agent needs help choosing subagents and dividing a larger task into clean delegated threads.
- `agent-room-executor` - Use before any request that involves two or more agents, agent debate, multi-agent review, multi-agent implementation, or choosing between Agent Room, Superpowers, Compound Engineering, and g-stack.
- `ai-engineer` - Use when a task needs implementation or debugging of model-backed application features, agent flows, or evaluation hooks.
- `angular-architect` - Use when a task needs Angular-specific help for component architecture, dependency injection, routing, signals, or enterprise application structure.
- `api-designer` - Use when a task needs API contract design, evolution planning, or compatibility review before implementation starts.
